Many + Functionalities
There are 2 types of Polymorphism
 1. Compile time polymorphism ( Early Binding )
 2. Run Time polymorphism ( Late Binding )


1. Compile Time Polymorphism
   It is method overloading -> two methods same name different number of arguments
2. Run time polymorphism
    It is method Overriding -> two methods same name same number of arguments
    but which method to run is decided by dynamic method dispatch

=====================================================================================
Dynamic method dispatch

it works on the basis of type of object  (Class of which the object is created)
Agar parent class A me koi  method hai , aur A kaa child B hai aur B me bhi same method hai
then main function me jis Kisi kaa bhi object bnega uska hi method run hoga.


Also keep in mind :-

    If we are referring to a class A and made the object of B then it is fine only if B is a child of A
    otherwise not
    like
    A obj = new B(); // ok if b is extending a;
    and
    there exist another class D not extending any class
    obj = new D() --> this will not be allowed because
    obj is the reference varible of A so it can only be assigned to relatives of A.